name: Avignon
description:
Box office and merry-go-round in the rain. Place de l'Horloge, Avignon.

This archival work is printed on heavy 330gsm matte paper which is 100% acid free, lignin free and chlorine free. 

The size options refer to the size of the paper.  The image is printed with a small border for framing.

name: Manic Street Preachers (1992) work print
description:
Manic Street Preachers live at Stoke Poly on 1 February 1992, touring the album Generation Terrorists.

This is an original B/W work print on pearl fiber-based paper, printed by me in an actual darkroom circa 1992. Work print means it was one of the first prints I made of the image for reference and was not the final or master print. The nature of a work print is that it might have idiosyncrasies not found on a final print. On this print I wrote "Manic St Preachers ca/1992 Stoke, UK copyright Liane, credit and copyright reserved" on the back in blue marker.

Image is printed full-frame, has keyline showing, and measures 6.5x10" on a 9.5x12" piece of paper.
